cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper discusses the applications of kernel PCA in face recognition and active shape models, which are both related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance comparison between kernel PCA and standard PCA, which is related to machine learning and data analysis, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of kernel PCA in constructing human face models, which is related to multimedia and graphics, so cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the reconstruction of pre-images for kernel PCA, which is related to neural networks and deep learning, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category.
